BFN 

  [Text] Kazakh Foreign Minister Kanat Saudabayev, who is 
participating in the conference of foreign ministers of the 
North Atlantic Cooperation Council in Istanbul, met President of 
Turkey Suleyman Demirel, U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev, and 
British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd today. They discussed 
bilateral relations, and topical international and regional 
problems. Also today, Kanat Saudabayev received James Collins, 
the U.s. Ambassador-at-large for the CIS. A frank and detailed 
conversation was held on issues of mutual interest. 

